  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the prevalence, etiology, and timing of missed
      Serious Medical Illness (SMI) in patients referred to adult psychiatry by emergency
      physicians, as well as to determine admission rates for SMI soon after discharge from an
      inpatient psychiatry admission.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
